# Platform Core Engineering

- Use existing repo architecture before introducing new patterns.
- Keep changes scoped and avoid broad refactors unless requested.
- Prefer typed APIs and explicit return types for shared utilities.
- Reuse shared code from `packages/*` before duplicating logic in apps.
- Do not add dependencies unless clearly justified and aligned with monorepo usage.
- Preserve SSR-safe behavior and avoid browser-only code in server contexts.
- Use `eslint` and `typescript` feedback as source of truth for correctness.
- Keep implementation-focused prompts concise; avoid roleplay/persona boilerplate.
- Treat each client app as a distinct brand; never copy another client's page layout or styling by default.

## Icons (client marketing sites)

- Use **Remix Icon** as the default icon set—same as `@sweetmedia/inner-peak-colorado` and `@sweetmedia/sweet-media`: `<i className="ri-*-line">` with the stylesheet from **`https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/remixicon@4.6.0/fonts/remixicon.css`** (load via `layout.tsx` pattern shared with `apps/client-template` / `apps/cipher-billing` / `apps/inner-peak-colorado`).
- Prefer **`npm`/`pnpm` icon packages only when Remix does not cover the glyph**; avoid mixing multiple general-purpose icon libraries in one app.
